[src:ninja-build/manual-p01] A `build` or `default` statement is first parsed as a space-separated list of filenames and then each name is expanded.
[src:ninja-build/manual-p01] This means that spaces within a variable will result in spaces in the expanded filename.
[src:ninja-build/manual-p01] In a `name = value` statement, whitespace at the beginning of a value is always stripped.
[src:ninja-build/manual-p01] Whitespace at the beginning of a line after a line continuation is also stripped.
[src:ninja-build/manual-p01] Other whitespace is only significant if it’s at the beginning of a line.
[src:ninja-build/manual-p01] If a line is indented more than the previous one, it’s considered part of its parent’s scope; if it is indented less than the previous one, it closes the previous scope.
[src:ninja-build/manual-p01] Two variables are significant when declared in the outermost file scope.
